00:51:15.155 --> 00:51:19.426 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Quebec is the largest
Canadian province by land area.

00:51:19.426 --> 00:51:21.762 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
This is home

00:51:21.762 --> 00:51:25.031 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
to more than
24,000 brothers and sisters.

00:51:25.031 --> 00:51:29.035 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The province is known
for its natural beauty:

00:51:29.035 --> 00:51:33.974 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
the St. Lawrence River,
thousands of lakes, waterfalls, ski slopes, 

00:51:33.974 --> 00:51:35.976 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and forests.

00:51:35.976 --> 00:51:37.744 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Quebec is rich with wildlife:

00:51:37.744 --> 00:51:40.247 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
moose, caribou,

00:51:40.247 --> 00:51:42.749 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
beavers, wolves,

00:51:42.749 --> 00:51:45.252 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and the Snowy Owl.

00:51:45.252 --> 00:51:48.722 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Jehovah’s people
began preaching here in the 1920’s.

00:51:48.722 --> 00:51:50.657 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Government opposition

00:51:50.657 --> 00:51:54.561 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
stirred up by the clergy
began almost immediately.

00:51:54.561 --> 00:51:56.563 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
In 1946,

00:51:56.563 --> 00:51:59.666 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
our brothers held a 16-day campaign

00:51:59.666 --> 00:52:02.736 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
to publicize the State’s disregard

00:52:02.736 --> 00:52:04.771 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
for freedom of worship.

00:52:04.771 --> 00:52:08.909 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
That led to the arrest
of hundreds of Jehovah’s Witnesses.

00:52:08.909 --> 00:52:10.944 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The first to be tried

00:52:10.944 --> 00:52:14.815 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
were Brother Aimé Boucher
and his two daughters,

00:52:14.815 --> 00:52:18.685 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
one of whom was just 11 years of age.

00:52:18.685 --> 00:52:20.821 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
In 1950,

00:52:20.821 --> 00:52:23.990 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
the Supreme Court
of Canada ruled in their favor,

00:52:23.990 --> 00:52:26.860 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
legally establishing
the right of Jehovah’s Witnesses

00:52:26.860 --> 00:52:30.030 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
to preach in Quebec.

00:52:30.030 --> 00:52:34.334 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Today, our brothers
are taking full advantage of this freedom.

00:52:34.334 --> 00:52:39.306 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Montreal is the province’s largest city.

00:52:39.306 --> 00:52:41.308 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Publishers enjoy public witnessing

00:52:41.308 --> 00:52:45.145 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
in Montreal’s popular
tourist areas, subway system,

00:52:45.145 --> 00:52:49.082 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and ports,
where workers come from many countries.

00:52:49.082 --> 00:52:51.017 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
They preach to students

00:52:51.017 --> 00:52:55.488 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
attending the city’s eight universities
and many colleges.

00:52:55.488 --> 00:52:58.992 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
In Quebec City, they even preach
in front of the government buildings

00:52:58.992 --> 00:53:03.330 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
where decades ago
laws were written to stop our work.

00:53:03.330 --> 00:53:07.334 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Brother Boucher was
from the small town of Lac-Etchemin.

00:53:07.334 --> 00:53:10.337 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
There are 71 publishers

00:53:10.337 --> 00:53:12.205 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
in the congregation here.

00:53:12.205 --> 00:53:14.341 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Their vast territory

00:53:14.341 --> 00:53:18.411 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
includes a lot of farmland,
but their hard work to reach everyone

00:53:18.411 --> 00:53:21.648 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
has produced several Bible studies.

00:53:22.482 --> 00:53:25.085 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The average midwinter temperature here

00:53:25.085 --> 00:53:27.721 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
is about minus 12 degrees Celsius,

00:53:27.721 --> 00:53:32.692 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
or about 10 degrees Fahrenheit,
and it often gets much colder.

00:53:32.692 --> 00:53:34.928 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Despite the temperature,

00:53:34.928 --> 00:53:38.732 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
our brothers enjoy warm association.

00:53:38.732 --> 00:53:43.536 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Quebec produces more than 70 percent
of the world’s maple syrup.

00:53:44.371 --> 00:53:47.440 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
A favorite candy is maple taffy

00:53:47.440 --> 00:53:49.476 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
—made by boiling the sap

00:53:49.476 --> 00:53:52.012 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
from maple trees,
pouring it onto snow,

00:53:52.012 --> 00:53:56.283 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
letting it harden,
and then rolling it onto a stick.

00:53:57.217 --> 00:54:01.321 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Our brothers and sisters
in the Lac-Etchemin Congregation

00:54:01.321 --> 00:54:05.325 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
